I"­<p>In trading jargon, <strong>ATH</strong> stands for <strong>All-Time High</strong>.</p>

<p>A market makes a new all-time high if its price action rises above the previous all-time maximum price. There is no other requirement for timeframe, <a href="/glossary/pattern-trading/">patterns</a> or any special <a href="/technical-analysis/">technical setup</a>. Even if the market retraces abruptly, the new ATH still counts.</p>

